profile_positions.description:
As the Payload Manager for The GMES Sentinel-1 Project in the Earth Observation Department I am in charge of monitoring the Sentinel-1A and Sentinel 1B payload related activities within the Industrial consortium and liaising with the Agency internal and external entities, with the objective of ensuring that the Sentinel-1 Payload fulfills the Agency's requirements, remains compatible with the Sentinel-1 mission, the spacecraft and the associated ground segment and is successfully commissioned in orbit.
I am also responsible for leading the Payload section and my duties include:
•	Maintaining the requirements for Sentinel-1;
•	Monitoring and controlling the industrial activities related to the development and procurement of the Sentinel-1A and Sentinel-1B Payloads;
•	Preparation, review, acceptance and monitoring of the payload assembly, integration, characterization, calibration and verification approach;
•	Participation with the Sentinel-1 Project team in the definition and implementation of the space segment, in the areas related to the payload, particularly in the definition and implementation of the interfaces with the spacecraft, the AIV activities, the on-ground and in-orbit system calibration and the definition of interfaces with the ground segment;
•	Maintaining technical and management interfaces with ESOC and ESRIN, for the exploitation of the Sentinel-1A and Sentinel-1B Payload, with respect to the operations and ground segment interface aspects;
•	Ensuring a smooth operation of the Sentinel-1 Payload section through effective leadership practices.
